Mxolisi Mngadi, News24(Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - A 2-year-old boy died after he was electrocuted in Kenville, north of Durban, police said on Wednesday.The toddler was electrocuted by live electric wires while he was playing with other children near his home where he lived with his grandmother, on Smithfield Road. The incident happened on Wednesday at about 14:30.KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said an inquest docket had been opened and Greenwood Park police were investigating the circumstances around the incident. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.